@startuml Sequence_Search_Filter

actor User
participant "Client" as Client
participant "Product API" as API
participant "Database" as DB
participant "Redis Cache" as Cache

== Search Products ==
User -> Client: Enter search query
Client -> API: GET /api/shop/products?search=query
API -> Cache: Check cache

alt Cached results
    Cache --> API: Cached results
    API --> Client: Return cached data
else Not cached
    Cache --> API: Cache miss
    API -> DB: Search products
    DB --> API: Search results
    API -> Cache: Store in cache
    API --> Client: Return results
end

Client --> User: Display search results

== Filter Products ==
User -> Client: Apply filters
Client -> Client: Build filter params
Client -> API: GET /api/shop/products?category=X&price=Y&rating=Z
API -> DB: Query with filters
DB --> API: Filtered results
API -> DB: Sort results
DB --> API: Sorted results
API --> Client: Return filtered products
Client --> User: Display filtered list

== Pagination ==
User -> Client: Click next page
Client -> API: GET /api/shop/products?page=2
API -> DB: Get page 2
DB --> API: Page 2 results
API --> Client: Return paginated results
Client --> User: Display page 2

@enduml

